rComments: Great lecturer, who is able to convey the material well - but he is flippant and capricious outside of his lectures. That experience from poli-sci profs/TAs led me to pursue a major in the hard sciences instead. Instructors seem to be more willing to cultivate and guide students there. Nonetheless, I recommend his courses if you like poli theory.

As an international student from Singapore, it was such a breath of fresh air when attending Professor Lippincott's lectures. He is always on point, clear, descriptive and very eloquent. He has a witty, hilarious side as well, he is one of the few professors that made me enjoy Political Science and take it up as a major. Thank you sir!

I really enjoyed all of the lectures we had with Professor Lippincott. They were straightforward and crystal clear. However, I found it quiet difficult to write a 16 page essay in a short period of time.
Inspiring and amazing professor.   One of the FEW fond memories I have of this university.
Best Prof EVER.

Made the material relatable and easy-to-understand. His lecture style can be best described as a "Dummy's Guide to Political Ideology." Yes, he may have oversimplified some concepts, but they I found that deeper discussions of these concepts usually happen in tutorial. His lectures were good for keeping you on track on the big ideas.
Horrible lecture style, but if you read the summaries of the reading and pay attention you'll do fine.

Love him, he was clear and really knew what he was talking about. Never brought notes which made it a little hard to take my own notes since he spoke so quickly without having to read off his own notes.

Brilliant and inspiring! after taking his POL113 class first year I was hooked; i have taken all 4 of his classes every year since. Amazing lecture style - precise, non-biased and clever with an addition of witty sarcastic humor when appropriate.

Great prof. has lots of knowledge in his material. However, he will not give you a mark you deserves unless you suck up and talk to him alot. In his 400 level courses you can write brilliant essays but he will think you're clueless unless you talk in class. All his 400 level classes are based 100% on participation, all essays will match that mark
Great prof

Other students are right, he's a pretty funny guy and can make political theory actually not a terrible thing to listen to for 2 hours. But I don't know why everyone loves him, if your in his 3rd or 4th year classes, you realize that he marks students as if he actually teaches the material, and doesn't just spend the whole class cracking jokes.
Amazing Prof

As far as Professors go, Lippincott was the highlight of my University career. I took four of his classes. Not only was he a skilled and ethusiastic educator, but also a funny and down-to-earth guy. Do the readings, take quality lecture notes, and you should have no problem excelling in his classes. Lippincott gets an A+.
Best prof EVER!! Took POL200 AND POL203 with him. He makes the most dull material very interesting and fun. Approachable and cares about his students.
I had Lippincott in '06. Very good lecturer. Would definitely recommend his classes.
Amazing professor. One of the best at UofT, made the worst couse in political science interesting.
He is one the best teachers, I have ever had. Thanks UFT.

lippincot is the man! best professor ive had at u of t. im a commerce student and im jealous we dont have profs like lippincot. first off, hes a great lecturer. i actually found his lectures on US politics really entertaining. also, his tests are very fair, not easy but straightforward so if you put the work in you will do fine
One of the best!
Delivers political theory flawlessly!

Excellent sense of humor - funny, doesn't overdo it, and his laugh is probs the best part... Super enjoyable class, and he makes the information totally comprehensive and interesting - best prof at UofT.
Who knew Politics could be so interesting?! This prof is probably the best at U of T, you'll really be missing out if you dont take AT LEAST ONE class with him!

I think the best thing about him is that he shares the same contempt I have for stupid questions... LOL. Obviously he doesn't say so, but you can tell that a stupid question has been asked cause he gets this kind of "are you kidding me" grin on his face. Great prof, he's gonna make POL200 alot easier to take.

Fantastic prof. Best POL course I've ever taken, and I would recommend any class Lippincott teaches. Lectures are really the highlight and I think it's a huge shame & waste of money if you don't go, because they really are that good. Lippincott is entertaining, funny, and very knowledgable. GO TO CLASS & you'll kill the course.

He is THE BEST professor I've had in Pol Sci so far (it's my 6th pol course). He can turn something so abstract and complex into something so real and easy to relate to. And there will always be something to laugh at and he's not even trying! I'd recommend him to anyone taking POL200 or POL320!
Very knowledgable and engaging. An excellent prof to have!

Good lectures.  Most of them are lively and clear, but sometimes they go a little off-topic.  Tests are straightforward and fair, no essays.  Encourages questions in class but isn't the type of prof who actually wants to talk to students outside the classroom.  Worse part was actually the irrelevant questions students asked.
An excellent Prof...makes material highly interesting, funny and TEACHES the material in a fashion that makes learning easy. Tests are reasonable if you attend class and study.

Prof. Lippincott is possibly one the best professors i've ever had. Lectures are very clear, and his style of lecturing make you want to attend. Always a pleasure going to lectures. Tests are fair, and you will do well if you study the material, no tricks. Great class.

I had him in spring 2002, and it is still one of the most memorable courses I've ever taken. He was very well prepared, very careful in his choice of words and used very memorable examples and analogies to clarify his points. He always made sure we knew exactly what we had to do in order to do well. A great instructor.
Hilarious ... and SMART! really enjoyed his class
Brilliant man
Possibly the best political theory professor at UofT

Makes class extremely interesting. Great at lecturing - you WANT to attend. No points for attending tutorials. Tended to make fun of people who asked questions. Essays are fair - tests are either tricky or easy.
Great Prof, the best! Very smart, passes on his knowledge thru good use of examples. He is clear and expects his students to be clear as well.
he's awesome

An amazing class - one of the best ones I took while at U of T. Exams were straightforward and you can do well if you read and attend classes - NO surprises. Participation is optional which is GREAT - U of T places too much emphasis on participation marks - HILARIOUS - makes a 9am class worth it!

By far, the best professor I've ever had. I've taken two courses with him. He'll answer your question and he'll answer it well, but he's not going to coddle you, so grow up - this ain't highschool. Has the ability to explain concepts with exceptional clarity and great examples. Good sense of humour.

I loved Prof. Lippincott when I had him and I've only grown to appreciate him more and more in grad school. I find the understanding of classical pol theory texts is much more advanced (and less pretentious) than those of my fellow grad students. He cares about these texts and passes this on.
No Comments
Awesome lecturer (sarcasm is hilarious and effective; reminds me of the Daily Show)  Tests have no surprises.
I wish I could have taken POL200 with him! He's amazingly funny, incorporates a broad knowledge into the subject, and presents the material very clearly. He made political theory easy!
An amazing prof! Very funny and interesting - lectures got me hooked on political theory (which was no easy task..) His unconventional lecture style makes learning fun!

engaging and direct lecturer, can be overbearingly sarcastic at times but that's his charm, open to new ideas and willing to listen to student's points of view. you will learn alot in his class rather than just pandering to his tastes.

All profs are human.  unique outlook on politics that should open your eyes a bit.  Yes, he makes you  weary of asking questions if you are the sensitive type (as I am).  Just take his perspective in and temporarily suspend battling for your own.
very entertaining...really knows how to keep people interested in the material
Discourages questions by sometimes making fun of the questioner.  Very clear.  Great intro to American politics.  Tests are straightforward, no curveballs.

Pretty good prof, knows the material quite well and presents it in an interestign manner.  U of T must not be known for its spelling since the previous two tries no one could even spell his last name correctly.
He reminds me of David Letterman, and is slightly funnier.
This guy is hilarious in an crusty arrogant american~ish kind of way.  Reuven is a super TA too.  The lectures are memorable because of Lippencott's style.  Take the course with him.
Discourages questions because his interpretation of the text is shallow and fragile.
Lippecott rules. Best lecturer I've had in a while
No Comments
Great Prof.Makes things a lot simpler than the readings
best prof at UT funny and smart
good guy, but tries to hard to be entertaining

Second time he's teaching me.  He's just fabulous.
Very nice and helpful.  Funny and a good lecturer.
Very good lecturer. Very funny.  An ideal professor and truly engaging

Your friggen rock!!!
No Comments
Exellent, interesting lecturer.
great prof, only class i don't snooze in
Very good lecturer.  Very funny.  Very helpful and approachable.
An ideal professor and a truly engaging and thought-provoking class.
Best Lecturer on Campus!

His lectures were very good.  He is very nice and helpful too.  I was impressed.
